{
  "texts": [
    "LLMs have also been used to automatically extract information about characterised SARS-CoV-2 mutations from published scientific literature (Serna Garcıá et al., 2023).",
    "Their ability to generate plausible text has implications for academic publication and translational research, with associated bioethical considerations that remain to be explored in detail (Page et al., 2023; Coiera et al., 2023).",
    "AI offers exciting possibilities for diverse practices within the field of microbial genomics.",
    "There are plentiful demonstrations in research settings of its capabilities for analysis of genomic and associated data that exceed what can be achieved within a realistic amount of time and effort by human experts.",
    "Despite this, AI for pathogen genomics is not yet ubiquitous in public health and diagnostic laboratory operations."
  ]
}